                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/1398: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-22T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 22, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2287. Department does not intend, for the present, at least, to make any reply to
                    Foreign Office communication referred to in your 3657 of August 20, 7 p.m.
                    Please inform Heath that Department has every confidence in the accuracy of his
                    statements. It greatly appreciates the efficient help and extra time which you
                    and Heath gave to the handling of the entire matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
